The research results of students playing the leading role at the academic annual meeting of Zhejiang University make people's brains open-Xinhuanet
Wash your hands with air, judge diseases with breath, and accurately search for the source of smog. Last night, at the opening ceremony of the 2016 academic annual meeting of Zhejiang University, a series of academic achievements with big brains were commended.
The main researchers of these achievements are students, and the research covers various fields such as environment, machinery, energy, medical treatment, life science, humanities education, etc. The students started with a curious idea and created many high-end inventions with application value, some of which have won awards at home and abroad.
Biosensor: Your family doctor
Zhang Diming, a doctoral student at the School of Biomedical Engineering, showed a biosensor on the smart phone, which is only half the size of a smart phone.
"You only need to take a gentle breath, and this set of equipment can initially detect your health from the composition of the gas you exhale."
Zhang Diming said that this set of sensors is connected to the smart phone, and after exhaling the air, the health report will be displayed on the phone.
Smart bracelets that can detect health status on the market generally detect physical parameters such as temperature and pulse.
This set of biosensors uses graphene, a new material, and its target is chemical elements. Its keen "sense of smell" allows it to reflect the health status more deeply and accurately.
Intelligent operating lamp: doctors' high-energy eyes
In addition to smart phones, smart operating lamps are also used in the operating room.
The invention won a silver medal at the 44th International Invention Exhibition in Geneva, Switzerland this year.
The team of Zhu Linjing and Shen Junfei, master students of the School of Optoelectronic Science and Engineering, opened up new ideas in the defects of traditional surgical lamps and invented intelligent LED surgical shadowless lamps.
"The early detection and removal of many diseases are not in place, which is related to the lamps used by doctors in the operating room."
Shen Junfei said, for example, if doctors can't see all the tumor tissues in time during the early examination of cancer, then the cancer cells will spread later.
The intelligent surgical lamp has four lamp panels that enhance the difference between different tissues under light by adjusting the spectrum.
During the operation, doctors can adjust the size, brightness, spectrum, color uniformity and shadowless rate of the light spot at any time according to the needs of the operation and personal habits.
This intelligent operating lamp has been tried out in run Shaw Hospital Affiliated to Zhejiang University Medical College, Children's Hospital Affiliated to Zhejiang University Medical College and other hospitals, and has received good feedback.
Last October, the invention won the first prize of the National Challenge Cup.
Wash hands with air: water saving and cool
Ordinary people wash their hands with water, wipe some soap and squeeze some hand sanitizer, while Li Qizhang and other students invented a set of "air hand washing device".
As long as we stand on the installed sink, our weight can compress the air out.
"It's like a pump.
The compressed air forms a fluid at the faucet and combines with water.
In this way, we can wash our hands! "
Color reaction and bacterial residue experiments have proved that the effect of washing hands by this method is the same as that of ordinary hand washing methods.
This device only needs to rely on our own gravity as the drive, which can not only ensure the degree of cleaning, but also save 90% of water. The whole process is completely energy free, energy saving and environmental protection.
Last year, at the second Global Major Challenge Summit, the invention stood out among many of the world's top universities and won the only gold medal.
Chongqing secondary vocational school pilot modern apprenticeship enrollment is the prospective employees of the enterprise-Xinhuanet
Yesterday, the reporter learned from the Municipal Education Commission that starting from this year, the city will pilot the "modern apprenticeship" talent training mode in 60 secondary vocational schools. The students who receive the pilot training also have apprenticeship status. After enrollment, they will be pre-recorded as unit employees by the pilot enterprises.
The Municipal Education Commission requires that the enrollment procedures of secondary vocational schools and enterprise employment procedures be standardized, and the dual identities of secondary vocational school students and enterprise prospective employees of apprentices be clarified. According to the principle of two-way choice, apprentices, schools and enterprises sign a tripartite agreement. For apprentices who have reached the age of 16 but have not reached the age of 18, an agreement must be signed by apprentices, guardians, schools and enterprises to determine the rights and interests of all parties and the specific posts, teaching contents and rights and interests protection of apprentices on the job.
Pilot schools are encouraged to adopt a modern apprenticeship system to jointly carry out pre-job training and transfer training for enterprise employees with cooperative enterprises.
Pilot schools should reform the talent training mode.
Schools and enterprises jointly design talent training programs, and jointly formulate professional teaching standards, curriculum standards, post standards, enterprise master standards, quality monitoring standards and corresponding implementation plans.
The pilot takes the training academic system as a pilot cycle, and the internship time of students in the enterprise is determined according to the professional talent training plan, and the post internship is generally 6 months.
In enterprise practice, the enterprise team management mode should be implemented. According to the characteristics of different majors, a master can take 2 to 5 apprentices to form a study group to ensure that students master the skills required for each rotation training position.
According to the arrangement, from 2016 to August 2019, the city has identified 60 pilot modern apprenticeship in municipal secondary vocational schools in three batches, with about 50 people in each pilot and a total of about 3,000 students (apprentices) trained.
In accordance with the principle of pilot before implementation and gradually advancing from point to point, we will explore the establishment of a long-term mechanism of joint enrollment, joint training and integrated education between schools and enterprises, effectively improve students' post skills, and improve students' corresponding employment rate and employment quality.
