South African doctor: Although Omicron has strong transmission power, it is mostly mild
Many doctors and medical experts in South Africa believe that the disease caused by the Omicron variant of the novel coronavirus is more mild than the Delta variant, although it spreads faster.
With the spread of the Omicron variant in South Africa, a group of more than 5,000 doctors in Gauteng province, South Africa, reported that the COVID-19 patients they are currently treating have mild symptoms, such as body pain and cough, and other flu-like symptoms, the Associated Press said.
Dr. UnbenPillay, director of the group, said he sees dozens of patients every day, but none of them need to be hospitalized yet.
They were able to control the disease at home and most recovered within 10 to 14 days of isolation, Pillay said."
This includes elderly patients and those with health problems, who would otherwise be more likely to fall into severe illness due to coronavirus infection, he said.
In contrast, he said, the COVID-19 patients he treated in the last wave of Delta had "difficulty breathing and low blood oxygen levels.
Many people will be hospitalized in a few days."
Within two weeks of the first report of the Omicron mutant strain in southern Africa, other doctors shared similar experiences.
Although it will take several weeks to collect enough data, doctors' observations and early evidence provide some clues.
According to the South African National Institute of Infectious Diseases, only 30% of COVID-19 patients hospitalized in recent weeks are seriously ill, half the proportion of severe cases in the previous wave of outbreaks; the average length of stay has been shortened from 8 days to 2.8 days; only 3% of recent COVID-19 patients have died, compared with 20% of early outbreaks in South Africa.
Willem Hanekom, director of the African Institute of Health, quoted data from the National Institute of Infectious Diseases and other reports as saying: "at present, almost all indications are that this is a milder disease."
He also said: "It is still early and we need to get late data.
Usually, hospitalizations and deaths occur late, and we are only two weeks into this wave of outbreaks."
At the same time, scientists around the world are looking at case numbers and hospitalization rates while testing the effectiveness of current vaccines and treatments.
Although Delta remains the world's leading strain of COVID-19, Omicron cases are emerging in dozens of countries, with South Africa at the center of the outbreak.
Gauteng province saw a 400% increase in new cases detected in the first week of December, according to health officials, and tests showed that the Omicron variant accounted for more than 90% of cases.
Education Review: What does it take to save abducted children?
If we compare the famous public service slogan of "no sale, no killing", then in a good environment where there is no demand for "abduction", mass prevention and control, and anti-abduction by the whole people make abduction unprofitable, risky and costly, and such crimes will not happen frequently.
Recently, the emergency release platform for missing children information developed by the Criminal Investigation Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security was launched.
This is an Internet information platform created to establish an authoritative channel for the release of missing children information and find abducted children in a timely manner.
Hearing that this App is called "Reunion", I feel warm.
The new technical means are not only named "literature and art" and full of feelings, but also the information technology is used properly, practically and effective.
The primary goal of anti-abduction law enforcement is to find abducted children and protect their personal safety and freedom.
The second is the trial and punishment of suspects.
The meaning of criminal punishment, from individual punishment, social prevention to legal education, can list many "big words".
However, before the trafficking case is solved, priority should be given to the personal safety of the victims.
Under the urgent purpose of "seeking rescue", controversial topics such as "whether child abduction and trafficking should be subject to the death penalty" can be put on hold and discussed carefully; but the rescue of abducted children cannot wait.
According to the investigation experience of such cases, traffickers are used to staying away from the crime site as soon as possible after they succeed.
If the abduction search is delayed for one more minute, the child may be one step away from the parents, and the difficulty of case detection will increase by one point.
Under such circumstances, it is indeed a pragmatic action to come up with effective methods such as the "reunion" platform, which directly help to solve cases and find children.
After all, "anti-abduction" is a big task that requires the operation of the entire legal system.
To crack down on crime and protect the rights and interests of children and parents, from the improvement of legislation, to the protection of justice and the meticulous law enforcement, we all need to implement the care of "protecting the young and helping the weak".
In addition, the prevention of child trafficking, from the family to society, can be done better.
For example, in a common case, a family of three resting at the railway station, their parents slept soundly and woke up to find that their child was gone.
A two-year-old child cannot be expected to have enough self-protection skills, but as a parent of a young child, he should at least have a considerable sense of protection.
Parents take turns to rest, or put their children under safe protection, are the minimum means to prevent children from being abducted.
From the other side of the police's crackdown on trafficking crimes, the party who buys abducted children should also be paid attention to and punished.
A single illegal act is often just a link in a long chain.
According to the provisions of China's Criminal Law, the legal starting point for the crime of abducting and trafficking in children is 5 years; if the circumstances are especially serious, they may be sentenced to death and confiscation of property.
The starting point is high and the maximum punishment is heavy. Under the general trend of "light punishment", the crime of abducting and trafficking in children obviously belongs to the crime of heavier punishment.
But there are still many cases of abduction and trafficking every year.
It can be seen that some people have backward concepts and weak legal awareness in raising children.
The legal education of these people should be followed up at the same time.
To effectively control the crime of abduction and trafficking, we cannot rely solely on strict official law enforcement.
If the "market" of abduction exists widely, the traffickers are greedy for profit, constantly innovate the means of abduction, and form a situation of "fighting law" with law enforcers, the anti-abduction action is bound to fall into the quagmire of inefficiency.
Therefore, getting rid of backward concepts and popularizing legal common sense will also help to eradicate the crime of abduction, trafficking and buying children.
