At present, the trend of informationization and internationalization of higher education is becoming increasingly obvious, and the global competition in education, science and technology and talents is intensifying. As an important "supply side", the structural reform of higher education is facing unprecedented opportunities and challenges.
In particular, the proposal of "the overall plan to promote the construction of world-class universities and first-class disciplines" not only shows China's confidence and determination to move forward from a big country in higher education to a powerful country in higher education, but also puts forward higher and newer requirements for the development of universities.
How to strive to become one of the world's first-class universities in a relatively short period of time, speed up the construction of a number of world-class universities and a number of world-class disciplines on the basis of a certain gap, and achieve "corner overtaking"?
