Kailu Aminus revealed that the latest batch of anti-counterfeiting paper arrived in Kuala Lumpur on the 6th of this month, and then handed it over to the printing company on the 8th for some printing work.
"The bureau will send someone to Kuala Lumpur to pick up the goods next Thursday, and return to Sabah for the final stage of printing immediately. It is estimated that it will be handed over to the applicant in two more working days (December 20)."
"We will inform applicants to go to local branches to collect birth registration paper."
He added that Sabah has issued a total of 24,801 birth papers so far this year.
