Don't scare people at the starting line-Xinhuanet
When you visit the book market, you can often feel the popularity of successful books.
Many of today's success books preach the "best principle"-that is, assuming or implying that you can "do it" before telling you what you need to do.
It means that we have suddenly passed the most important and fundamental link of "how to do it".
Because of this, these books all have one thing in common-either do your best in one go, or do nothing at all; it's either 100 or 0; either you climb Mount Tai, or you just stay where you are.
This "best principle" will make anyone admit that it is "extremely correct", but 99% of people will be intimidated before the starting line.
Because this theory advocates a path of "you have to make up your mind, be a new person, and make a 180-degree change", which is precisely the fatal weakness of many people.
For those who stick to the rules, follow the old ways, and refuse to change, you have to shout "you want to change" in his ear, which is undoubtedly self-deception and casting pearls before swine.
The vast majority of people will be timid in front of the word "change", stagnant, and difficult to make up their minds; or with a temporary impulse, they have made a painful determination to "change" and bravely took the first step, but often the good times do not last long, and they will not be defeated for a long time, so it is difficult to see sustainability.
Mr. Ma Sanli's famous crosstalk "from Tomorrow" is the most vivid expression of this "universal humanity" classic.
The biggest problem with the "best principle" is that the threshold is too high, which often exceeds the ability limit of ordinary people and makes most people "look at the door and sigh".
Perhaps the "second best principle" is a way to put more ordinary people on the road to relative success.
The core of the "second best principle" lies in "lowering the threshold"-it encourages a theory of "accumulating small wins into big wins", that is, if you can't do 100, you can only do 1: because 1 is always greater than 0; If you can't climb Mount Tai, just climb the small sand dunes in front of your house, because it's better than standing still.
In short, as long as you do something, it's better than nothing.
As the threshold is greatly reduced, there is more possibility for ordinary people to persist, and as long as they persist in everything, the probability of success will increase.
It's just that the road to success following the "second best principle" is a little longer.
All in all, although the "best principle" is ostensibly under the banner of making everyone successful, it can actually motivate a few in the end; while the "second best principle" can effectively motivate more people and benefit as many people as possible.
Qinghai Lake naked carp resource reserves increased by 7,100 tons this year-Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Xining, December 11 (reporters Luo Xiaofei, Zhang Hongxiang) the reporter learned from the Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs that the latest monitoring results show that the reserves of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake increased by 7,100 tons this year compared with the previous year, reaching 108,500 tons, a cumulative increase of more than 40 times compared with the initial stage of protection in 2002.
Naked carp in Qinghai Lake, commonly known as "Huangyu", is a unique and precious fish species in Qinghai Lake, which plays an important role in maintaining the safety and biodiversity of the "water-fish-bird" ecological chain in Qinghai Lake Basin.
In the 1960 s and 1970 s, affected by a large number of human hunting and the increasing degradation of the environment in the breeding waters of naked carp, the number of naked carp in Qinghai Lake decreased sharply. In 2002, the reserves of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake were only 2592 tons.
In 2004, Qinghai Lake naked carp was listed as an endangered species in the Red List of Chinese Species.
Since 2003, Qinghai Province has closed the lake for fish breeding, prohibiting any unit, collective or individual from fishing for naked carp in Qinghai Lake and its main rivers and tributaries, and prohibiting the sale of naked carp and its products.
At the same time, through artificial proliferation and release, cleaning up the main rivers entering Qinghai Lake, designing scientific and reasonable "fish passage" and other measures to continuously strengthen protection, the reserves of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake have increased year by year.
Yang Lin, deputy director of the Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, said that up to now, nearly 180 million naked carp in Qinghai Lake have been artificially multiplied and released, contributing more than 23% to the recovery of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake.
The source area of the three rivers in Qinghai is an important ecological barrier and water conservation area in China and even in Asia, while Qinghai Lake is a natural barrier and ecological function area to control the eastward spread of desertification in the west.
In order to protect the ecological environment of the source areas of the three rivers and the waters of Qinghai Lake, protect aquatic wildlife, and maintain the biodiversity of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, Qinghai has successively issued a ban on fishing in the key waters of the Yangtze River, the Yellow River and Qinghai Lake since the beginning of this year, and established a comprehensive ban management system of "one river, one river and one lake".
