Xinhua News Agency, Tianjin, December 12 (Reporter Zhou Runjian) Astronomical science experts said that as the last large-scale meteor shower of the year, the Geminid meteor shower, one of the three major meteor showers in the northern hemisphere, will usher in a great deal on December 14. Friends who like meteor showers can observe it in the middle of the night.
Beijing astronomy enthusiast an Jiu photographed the Geminid meteor shower in Qinghai on December 13, 2018.
The parent body of most meteor showers is a periodic comet, but the parent body of the Geminid meteor shower is asteroid Phaeton 3200, an Apollo-type asteroid.
The Geminid meteor shower is also the second known meteor shower that is not "bred" by comets.
Xiu Lipeng, director of the Tianjin Astronomical Society and an expert in astronomical science popularization, said that just like the New Year's blockbuster, Geminid meteor showers generally appear at the end of the year, and the "release schedule" can last from December 4 to 17.
This meteor shower is famous for its large and stable flow. Together with the quadrant meteor shower and the Perseid meteor shower, it is known as the three major meteor showers in the Northern Hemisphere.
A significant feature of the Geminid meteor shower is that meteors are slow, colorful and have many fire meteors, which is suitable for both visual and beginners of astronomical photography.
Tianjin astronomy enthusiast Yang Jing takes a Geminid meteor shower in Jizhou, Tianjin on December 13, 2020.
Astronomical forecasts show that this year's Geminid meteor shower will usher in a maximum at around 15:00 on December 14, with a maximum ZHR (the number of meteors that can be seen per hour when the radiation point is directly above the head under ideal observation conditions) of 150.
Geminid meteor shower recommended index chart.
"Last year, people were deeply impressed by the colorful Geminid meteor shower, but this year's Geminid meteor shower will be disturbed by moonlight, which will be a little less exciting.
The 14th is November 11th of the lunar calendar, and the moon phase is a full and convex moon. Bright moonlight will interfere with the observation. Fortunately, the moon will set in the second half of the night, when the radiation point of the Geminid meteor shower will also rise relatively high.
Friends who like meteor showers can observe in the last few hours after the moon, but pay attention to cold and warm protection."
How can we observe as many meteors as possible?
"It is not recommended to observe in the city. You can choose a place with high altitude, low light damage and a wide field of vision facing the northeast in the suburbs or rural areas, and then wait patiently until the moon sets and observe visually.
It should be noted that the Geminid meteor shower has a large flow in all directions, so you don't have to stare at the radiation point of the Geminid meteor shower all the time during observation.
Friends who like photography want to shoot a gorgeous' meteor shower blockbuster', it is best to choose a wide-angle, large aperture lens, and use high ISO and maximum aperture when shooting.
Based on stability and continuity considerations, a tripod, spare battery and shutter cable are also essential."
Xiu Lipeng reminded.
